1
00:00:02,936 --> 00:00:04,404
Uh...

2
00:00:04,505 --> 00:00:05,872
Huh?

3
00:00:05,972 --> 00:00:09,610
(Anzai grunting)

4
00:01:43,103 --> 00:01:44,337
[HANS]
He transformed!

5
00:01:44,437 --> 00:01:46,472
But he didn't drink
a drop of blood.

6
00:01:46,573 --> 00:01:48,509
(Anzai hisses)

7
00:01:49,375 --> 00:01:51,778
[HANS]
<i>I have to get Tsukasa‐</i>

8
00:01:51,878 --> 00:01:53,680
<i>He dodged me!</i>

9
00:01:53,780 --> 00:01:55,048
Hey!

10
00:01:55,148 --> 00:01:56,783
Didn't you just tell me
if you transformed,

11
00:01:56,883 --> 00:01:57,884
I was to keep her safe?

12
00:01:57,984 --> 00:01:59,385
You need to hand
her over now!

13
00:01:59,485 --> 00:02:01,087
Look... she might be hurt.

14
00:02:01,187 --> 00:02:02,455
She needs to get some help!

15
00:02:02,556 --> 00:02:04,791
Are you even listening to me?

16
00:02:05,792 --> 00:02:07,460
Ah it's you... Anzai...

17
00:02:07,561 --> 00:02:11,497
I... I thought I... I was...

18
00:02:11,598 --> 00:02:14,300
That I was shot in the stomach.

19
00:02:15,536 --> 00:02:18,138
The bullet... stuck in here.

20
00:02:18,238 --> 00:02:19,405
[ANZAI]
(Angst)

21
00:02:19,506 --> 00:02:21,508
I had this right where
it hit me!

22
00:02:21,608 --> 00:02:25,946
It was... hers...
the sniper gave it
to me earlier today.

23
00:02:26,046 --> 00:02:27,648
I have to‐

24
00:02:27,748 --> 00:02:29,315
(Anzai crying)

25
00:02:29,415 --> 00:02:33,620
[HANS]
<i>He regained his sanity</i>
<i>while still transformed.</i>

26
00:02:33,720 --> 00:02:35,055
<i>Amazing...</i>

27
00:02:35,155 --> 00:02:36,557
<i>If he went through</i>
<i>the proper training,</i>

28
00:02:36,657 --> 00:02:39,860
<i>he might learn to</i>
<i>really control himself.</i>

29
00:02:39,960 --> 00:02:41,227
[ZERO SIX]
Permission to fire?

30
00:02:41,327 --> 00:02:43,797
[ZERO TWO]
Granted. Take care
of it, Zero Six.

31
00:02:43,897 --> 00:02:45,231
(Gunshots)

32
00:02:45,331 --> 00:02:46,967
[ANZAI]
<i>Huh?</i>

33
00:02:47,067 --> 00:02:49,670
<i>I know that face. Makimura?</i>

34
00:02:49,770 --> 00:02:50,637
(Gunshot)

35
00:02:50,737 --> 00:02:52,205
(Anzai gasps)

36
00:02:55,842 --> 00:02:58,378
[NANAKO]
If only they were all like that.

37
00:02:58,478 --> 00:03:01,915
I wish all devil‐human
couples were like you two.

38
00:03:03,149 --> 00:03:05,451
[TSUKASA]
Did she say something to us?

39
00:03:05,552 --> 00:03:09,022
Our work here is done.
Let's pack it up.

40
00:03:09,122 --> 00:03:10,524
[KENICHI]
Are you okay?

41
00:03:10,624 --> 00:03:12,759
I'm fine, I'm not really hurt.

42
00:03:12,859 --> 00:03:14,094
Not that.

43
00:03:14,194 --> 00:03:16,697
That was your first time...
shooting a human.

44
00:03:16,797 --> 00:03:18,398
Was it hard?

45
00:03:19,099 --> 00:03:20,834
Not especially, no.

46
00:03:20,934 --> 00:03:24,170
It's wasn't that much different
from taking out devils.

47
00:03:24,270 --> 00:03:26,507
I see, well in that case...

48
00:03:26,607 --> 00:03:30,977
It's because I'm shooting
from a distance.

49
00:03:31,077 --> 00:03:34,347
So does Tsukasa always
administer your
sedatives for you?

50
00:03:34,447 --> 00:03:35,849
I've only done it twice.

51
00:03:35,949 --> 00:03:39,319
But it's a good idea for me
to be able to do it, right?

52
00:03:39,419 --> 00:03:41,221
I called the cops.

53
00:03:41,321 --> 00:03:45,058
I let them know there
were people with guns
on the roofs of two hotels.

54
00:03:45,158 --> 00:03:47,594
I didn't say anything
about Ushio, though.

55
00:03:47,694 --> 00:03:48,762
That good?

56
00:03:48,862 --> 00:03:51,397
Uh... I can't figure out
what we should do.

57
00:03:51,497 --> 00:03:53,266
I'll have to ask Sawazaki.

58
00:03:53,366 --> 00:03:54,300
[HANS]
Aye‐aye.

59
00:03:54,400 --> 00:03:55,135
[ANZAI]
Tsukasa.

60
00:03:55,235 --> 00:03:56,269
Uh... yeah?

61
00:03:56,369 --> 00:03:58,371
I need to talk to you for a sec.

62
00:03:58,471 --> 00:04:00,306
[TSUKASA]
Um‐sure...

63
00:04:00,406 --> 00:04:01,542
[HANS]
Hm?

64
00:04:01,642 --> 00:04:03,143
Hey, can I play with you two!

65
00:04:03,243 --> 00:04:04,511
[BOY]
Whoa! Where are you from?

66
00:04:04,611 --> 00:04:06,079
[OTHER BOY]
Your hair looks funny!

67
00:04:06,179 --> 00:04:08,782
[ANZAI]
There's this doctor,
a friend of Yanagi's.

68
00:04:08,882 --> 00:04:11,918
He told me in order to control
the devil inside me,

69
00:04:12,018 --> 00:04:13,253
I had to know myself.

70
00:04:13,353 --> 00:04:14,755
That it's important
to figure out

71
00:04:14,855 --> 00:04:16,790
exactly what causes
me to transform...

72
00:04:16,890 --> 00:04:20,260
And just how far
my transformation will go.

73
00:04:21,127 --> 00:04:22,328
But to be honest...

74
00:04:22,428 --> 00:04:24,297
I've never thought
about it that way.

75
00:04:24,397 --> 00:04:25,699
I didn't want to hurt you,

76
00:04:25,799 --> 00:04:27,267
so I always thought
it would be best

77
00:04:27,367 --> 00:04:29,503
if I just tried to
keep you at a distance.

78
00:04:29,603 --> 00:04:32,372
But every time I transform,
it's because of you.

79
00:04:32,472 --> 00:04:35,208
So if I want to learn more
about why I transform...

80
00:04:35,308 --> 00:04:37,878
(Boys ooh's and ahh's)
I'm going to have to
drag you in with me.

81
00:04:37,978 --> 00:04:41,615
But I fear it means
putting you in more danger.

82
00:04:41,715 --> 00:04:44,651
And I would never
want to do that to you.

83
00:04:45,952 --> 00:04:47,387
I now realized

84
00:04:47,487 --> 00:04:50,490
I've never actually
talked to you about this.

85
00:04:51,491 --> 00:04:52,793
[TSUKASA]
Back at the hotel,

86
00:04:52,893 --> 00:04:56,329
it was just like when you
saved me at college.

87
00:04:57,130 --> 00:04:58,999
You knew I was bleeding then,

88
00:04:59,099 --> 00:05:00,867
but you still came to help me.

89
00:05:00,967 --> 00:05:04,605
This time, I was shot, and well
I could have been bleeding.

90
00:05:04,705 --> 00:05:07,508
I was so happy
that you came for me.

91
00:05:07,608 --> 00:05:09,275
I really wanted to see you.

92
00:05:09,375 --> 00:05:10,644
(Anzai groans)

93
00:05:10,744 --> 00:05:12,779
[ANZAI]
If I had lost it and bitten you,

94
00:05:12,879 --> 00:05:15,882
do you honestly think you would
still be able to say that?

95
00:05:15,982 --> 00:05:18,484
I mean it probably wouldn't
just end right there.

96
00:05:18,585 --> 00:05:20,787
Devil's drink blood
and can do much worse.

97
00:05:20,887 --> 00:05:22,789
[TSUKASA]
I'm pretty sure Lee
would have stopped you

98
00:05:22,889 --> 00:05:24,791
before that
would have happened.

99
00:05:24,891 --> 00:05:27,894
Isn't that why you brought
him along with you today?

100
00:05:27,994 --> 00:05:30,463
Kind of like insurance,
just in case.

101
00:05:30,564 --> 00:05:32,132
Look don't worry.

102
00:05:32,232 --> 00:05:33,734
I don't think one
or two little bites

103
00:05:33,834 --> 00:05:35,636
is necessarily
going to kill me.

104
00:05:35,736 --> 00:05:39,640
Uh...
Well a bite is painful.

105
00:05:39,740 --> 00:05:42,543
<i>Was she always this reliable?</i>

106
00:05:42,643 --> 00:05:45,879
Physical pain doesn't
really bother me.

107
00:05:45,979 --> 00:05:49,916
I find it much harder not
being able to be around you.

108
00:05:50,016 --> 00:05:52,152
[ANZAI]
<i>Oh... of course.</i>

109
00:05:52,252 --> 00:05:54,555
<i>It was never about</i>
<i>her reliability...</i>

110
00:05:54,655 --> 00:05:56,322
<i>it's because she's sincere.</i>

111
00:05:56,422 --> 00:05:59,793
But, I guess I'm just being
kind of selfish with you.

112
00:05:59,893 --> 00:06:03,196
[TSUKASA]
I'm sorry. I know this
can't be easy.

113
00:06:03,296 --> 00:06:05,999
[ANZAI]
<i>And she never seems to lie.</i>

114
00:06:06,099 --> 00:06:10,003
You don't... think my face
is somewhat, disgusting?

115
00:06:10,103 --> 00:06:11,705
What? Why?

116
00:06:12,472 --> 00:06:14,340
D‐did somebody say it was?

117
00:06:14,440 --> 00:06:16,577
Don't let those people
bother you!

118
00:06:16,677 --> 00:06:18,512
They're just being cruel!

119
00:06:18,612 --> 00:06:19,913
It was me.

120
00:06:20,013 --> 00:06:21,281
Huh?

121
00:06:21,381 --> 00:06:25,118
The one who said I was
so disgusting was... me.

122
00:06:26,186 --> 00:06:28,088
Everyone thinks so.

123
00:06:28,188 --> 00:06:29,923
It's just you that's weird.

124
00:06:30,023 --> 00:06:32,425
It's dangerous for us
to be together.

125
00:06:32,526 --> 00:06:34,394
But I don't want to
leave you either.

126
00:06:34,494 --> 00:06:37,163
You might run off
and hurt yourself.

127
00:06:37,263 --> 00:06:39,199
That doctor told me.

128
00:06:39,299 --> 00:06:43,236
There are ways out there
that will enable you to
control your bloodlust.

129
00:06:43,336 --> 00:06:47,373
But to do that...
You're going to need
her help as well.

130
00:06:47,473 --> 00:06:48,709
[ANZAI]
Hm...

131
00:06:48,809 --> 00:06:50,410
I'm still a little concerned

132
00:06:50,511 --> 00:06:52,679
about what that could
possibly mean for us.

133
00:06:52,779 --> 00:06:56,016
How does one...
control the devil...?

134
00:06:58,719 --> 00:07:01,955
[TSUKASA]
Anzai... let's be together.

135
00:07:04,390 --> 00:07:06,259
I would like that.

136
00:07:06,359 --> 00:07:07,794
[BOYS]
‐ Bye!
‐ See ya!

137
00:07:07,894 --> 00:07:10,463
(Hans chuckling)
(Boys laughing)

138
00:07:11,665 --> 00:07:13,834
Um... so I was... thinking...

139
00:07:13,934 --> 00:07:15,836
[ANZAI]
Hm?

140
00:07:15,936 --> 00:07:17,237
Oh, nevermind!

141
00:07:17,337 --> 00:07:20,006
Wha...? Come on, now you're
just making me curious.

142
00:07:20,106 --> 00:07:21,575
I know... but...

143
00:07:21,675 --> 00:07:23,577
[ANZAI]
Just spit it out!

144
00:07:23,677 --> 00:07:26,479
Does... does this
mean that we're...

145
00:07:26,580 --> 00:07:28,414
actually like
a real couple now?

146
00:07:28,515 --> 00:07:31,317
[ANZAI]
<i>Whoa. That's true.</i>

147
00:07:31,417 --> 00:07:32,385
(Anzai laughing)

148
00:07:32,485 --> 00:07:33,887
Uh! What's so funny?

149
00:07:33,987 --> 00:07:35,956
"So, does this mean
we're a couple now?"

150
00:07:36,056 --> 00:07:37,691
Ah!

151
00:07:38,258 --> 00:07:40,761
Hm...

152
00:07:40,861 --> 00:07:42,529
[ANZAI]
<i>I guess we really</i>
<i>haven't talked about</i>

153
00:07:42,629 --> 00:07:44,931
<i>any of the</i>
<i>important stuff, have we?</i>

154
00:07:45,031 --> 00:07:46,633
You wanna be?

155
00:07:49,002 --> 00:07:50,604
Yes. I want to.

156
00:07:50,704 --> 00:07:53,339
Good... then I'm happy.

157
00:07:53,439 --> 00:07:54,941
So am I.

158
00:07:57,844 --> 00:08:00,246
Tsukasa... do you mind
if I just kiss you...

159
00:08:00,346 --> 00:08:01,347
Uh!

160
00:08:01,447 --> 00:08:03,183
[TSUKASA]
Mm!

161
00:08:04,685 --> 00:08:06,386
The sedative hasn't
worn off yet...

162
00:08:06,486 --> 00:08:08,989
so I don't think
I'll transform.
Yeah.

163
00:08:09,089 --> 00:08:10,591
Anzai's a bigger pervert
than he lets on.

164
00:08:10,691 --> 00:08:12,225
[TSUKASA]
Oh!

165
00:08:12,325 --> 00:08:14,160
You might wanna watch
yourself there, Tsukasa.

166
00:08:18,231 --> 00:08:19,866
[KATAGIRI]
Huh?

167
00:08:19,966 --> 00:08:22,035
Oh... I see.

168
00:08:22,135 --> 00:08:23,970
I'm sorry.

169
00:08:24,070 --> 00:08:27,508
[KIKUHARA]
So you're saying the manger
of Cross Bar, Kiwako Oe

170
00:08:27,608 --> 00:08:30,677
and her employee Wataru Akase,
are both dead?

171
00:08:30,777 --> 00:08:33,714
And Ryunosuke Katagiri
is in hiding?

172
00:08:33,814 --> 00:08:36,316
Though he's virtually
immobilized for now.

173
00:08:36,416 --> 00:08:40,220
Two people died because of him.
That should be warning enough.

174
00:08:40,320 --> 00:08:44,457
[USHIO ON RADIO]
<i>C Squad, Ushio here...</i>
<i>secure line.</i>

175
00:08:44,558 --> 00:08:47,594
<i>Zero Seven and Nine appear to</i>
<i>have escaped the Mino Hotel.</i>

176
00:08:47,694 --> 00:08:52,432
<i>The workers who went up</i>
<i>to inspect the water tank</i>
<i>had their uniforms stolen.</i>

177
00:08:52,533 --> 00:08:54,601
<i>They were left</i>
<i>tied up on the roof.</i>

178
00:08:54,701 --> 00:08:56,269
And what about the hostage?

179
00:08:56,369 --> 00:08:59,806
[USHIO]
<i>Um... a devil showed up</i>
<i>and took her away.</i>

180
00:08:59,906 --> 00:09:03,076
<i>Zero Six says it was</i>
<i>Anzai from F Squad.</i>

181
00:09:03,176 --> 00:09:05,445
[KIKUHARA]
<i>It's him...</i>
[USHIO] <i>What now?</i>

182
00:09:05,546 --> 00:09:08,414
[KIKUHARA]
We got a tip earlier from what
sounded like a young man.

183
00:09:08,515 --> 00:09:12,986
He said there were snipers
on the roof of both the
Mino Hotel and Grand Hotel.

184
00:09:13,086 --> 00:09:17,624
The blood splatter on the
roof will eventually tell them
that Makimura was involved.

185
00:09:17,724 --> 00:09:22,028
As for now... there was
nothing mentioned in the tip
about you being a spy.

186
00:09:22,128 --> 00:09:23,797
I wonder why...

187
00:09:23,897 --> 00:09:27,033
[KIKUHARA]
<i>I couldn't say. But Anzai's</i>
<i>just a low‐ranking officer.</i>

188
00:09:27,133 --> 00:09:29,936
<i>It may be that he couldn't</i>
<i>make the call on his own.</i>

189
00:09:30,036 --> 00:09:33,073
<i>We'll keep an eye on F Squad</i>
<i>for the time being.</i>

190
00:09:33,173 --> 00:09:34,575
Sounds good.

191
00:09:34,675 --> 00:09:36,710
[KIKUHARA]
<i>Can you find out</i>
<i>who the hostage was?</i>

192
00:09:36,810 --> 00:09:38,144
I'll find her.

193
00:09:38,244 --> 00:09:39,580
It's just a hunch but...

194
00:09:39,680 --> 00:09:42,849
I think Anzai and
the hostage are lovers.

195
00:09:42,949 --> 00:09:44,985
[KIKUHARA THINKING]
<i>Well... interesting.</i>

196
00:09:45,085 --> 00:09:47,387
<i>So he's old enough to</i>
<i>fall in love with a human,</i>

197
00:09:47,487 --> 00:09:49,189
<i>like his father.</i>

198
00:09:49,289 --> 00:09:51,324
<i>Aside from the hair color,</i>
<i>they look almost identical.</i>

199
00:09:51,424 --> 00:09:54,160
<i>Although, if he gets</i>
<i>to be any more like him...</i>

200
00:09:54,260 --> 00:09:55,896
<i>It would be tragic.</i>

201
00:09:55,996 --> 00:09:58,932
<i>The half‐devil son of</i>
<i>a violent mass murderer...</i>

202
00:09:59,032 --> 00:10:02,068
<i>My interest is piqued again...</i>

203
00:10:02,168 --> 00:10:04,638
<i>Yuuki Anzai.</i>

204
00:10:06,039 --> 00:10:07,774
After I move to
the place over the bar,

205
00:10:07,874 --> 00:10:09,375
we can see each other
every day.

206
00:10:09,475 --> 00:10:11,845
Yeah, I guess you're right.

207
00:10:12,979 --> 00:10:14,748
[ANZAI]
This place is a mess.

208
00:10:14,848 --> 00:10:16,817
They're supposed to
come fix it next month.

209
00:10:16,917 --> 00:10:18,652
[ANZAI]
Next month?

210
00:10:18,752 --> 00:10:20,453
Make sure to bring
your valuables.

211
00:10:20,554 --> 00:10:23,957
This place is just asking
to be robbed. Huh?

212
00:10:24,057 --> 00:10:25,626
[ANZAI]
You can take that, too.

213
00:10:25,726 --> 00:10:26,627
[TSUKASA]
Huh?

214
00:10:26,727 --> 00:10:28,061
(Taps foot)

215
00:10:28,161 --> 00:10:31,464
We won't be seeing this
place again for a while.

216
00:10:31,565 --> 00:10:32,966
[TSUKASA]
When it calms down,

217
00:10:33,066 --> 00:10:35,502
I hope we can relax
under the kotatsu again.

218
00:10:35,602 --> 00:10:36,570
[ANZAI]
Yeah.

219
00:10:36,670 --> 00:10:38,438
[SAWAZAKI]
That's fishy.

220
00:10:38,539 --> 00:10:42,108
He's not with the police.
It's an amateur stakeout.

221
00:10:42,208 --> 00:10:45,812
Could just be a nosy reporter...
trying to get a look at Tsukasa.

222
00:10:45,912 --> 00:10:49,115
A lot of people saw her
during the Ikebukuro incident.

223
00:10:49,215 --> 00:10:52,418
Some people have even leaked
her name and school, too.

224
00:10:52,519 --> 00:10:53,987
That's just great.

225
00:10:54,087 --> 00:10:55,822
[YANAGI]
Changing the subject.

226
00:10:55,922 --> 00:10:57,991
There are rumors going
around about a new group..

227
00:10:58,091 --> 00:10:59,793
they're trying to
wipe out the devils.

228
00:10:59,893 --> 00:11:01,427
What, are you serious?

229
00:11:01,528 --> 00:11:03,063
[YANAGI]
They're called the CCC.

230
00:11:03,163 --> 00:11:05,766
Known as the
Chosen Civil Community...

231
00:11:05,866 --> 00:11:08,802
[KANO]
So these lunkheads
think they're chosen, eh?

232
00:11:08,902 --> 00:11:10,236
Sounds sketchy.

233
00:11:10,336 --> 00:11:13,206
After the Ikebukuro Incident,
it's to be expected,

234
00:11:13,306 --> 00:11:16,176
groups like these are bound
to pop up during tragedy.

235
00:11:16,276 --> 00:11:17,811
Don't you think
it's a little too soon

236
